## Best Practices

1. Use consistent method names and signatures across platforms
2. Document platform-specific behaviors clearly
3. Convert platform-specific errors at the boundary
4. Implement graceful fallbacks for unsupported features
5. Test on all target platforms
6. Use feature flags for platform-specific code
7. Keep platform-specific code isolated
8. Share common code through trait implementations
9. Document supported features per platform
10. Provide meaningful error messages

